	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hi,
<br />I'd like to do a stereo mod on my NES.
<br />A lot of people go with the method described here:
<br /><a href="http://www.disgruntleddesigner.com/chrisc/nesstereo.html" class="postlink">http://www.disgruntleddesigner.com/chrisc/nesstereo.html</a>
<br />but I'd like to refrain from using the 2A07's outputs directly.
<br />
<br />What I'd like to do is to replicate part of the original audio circuitry, to separate the CPU from the external circuits.
<br />
<br />Here's what I came up with:
<br /><a href="http://circuits.kvee.cz/nes-audio-stereo.htm" class="postlink">http://circuits.kvee.cz/nes-audio-stereo.htm</a> (Java applet)
<br />or <a href="http://img528.imageshack.us/img528/3563/image1eg.png" class="postlink">http://img528.imageshack.us/img528/3563/image1eg.png</a> (screencap of the simulation)
<br />(transistors will be 2n3904, the 1k resistors are just test loads...)
<br />
<br />Here's my question: Will this work or will something explode? <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

